<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><Highlight kind="comment">/// LLVM Value Representation</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This is a very important LLVM class. It is the base class of all values</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><Highlight kind="comment">/// computed by a program that may be used as operands to other values. Value is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the super class of other important classes such as Instruction and Function.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="66"><Highlight kind="comment">/// All Values have a Type. Type is not a subclass of Value. Some values can</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><Highlight kind="comment">/// have a name and they belong to some Module.  Setting the name on the Value</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><Highlight kind="comment">/// automatically updates the module&#39;s symbol table.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Every value has a &quot;use list&quot; that keeps track of which other Values are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><Highlight kind="comment">/// using this Value.  A Value can also have an arbitrary number of ValueHandle</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><Highlight kind="comment">/// objects that watch it and listen to RAUW and Destroy events.  See</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><Highlight kind="comment">/// llvm/IR/ValueHandle.h for details.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value/#a18dbfcb332af7515599ee795cf462843">Value</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="692"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Accumulate the constant offset this value has compared to a base pointer.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="693"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Only &#39;getelementptr&#39; instructions (GEPs) are accumulated but other</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="694"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// instructions, e.g., casts, are stripped away as well.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The accumulated constant offset is added to \\p Offset and the base</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00696" /><CodeLine lineNumber="696"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// pointer is returned.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00697" /><CodeLine lineNumber="697"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00698" /><CodeLine lineNumber="698"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The APInt \\p Offset has to have a bit-width equal to the IntPtr type for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00699" /><CodeLine lineNumber="699"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the address space of &#39;this&#39; pointer value, e.g., use</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00700" /><CodeLine lineNumber="700"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// DataLayout::getIndexTypeSizeInBits(Ty).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00701" /><CodeLine lineNumber="701"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00702" /><CodeLine lineNumber="702"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// If \\p AllowNonInbounds is true, offsets in GEPs are stripped and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00703" /><CodeLine lineNumber="703"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// accumulated even if the GEP is not &quot;inbounds&quot;.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00704" /><CodeLine lineNumber="704"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00705" /><CodeLine lineNumber="705"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// If \\p AllowInvariantGroup is true then this method also looks through</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00706" /><CodeLine lineNumber="706"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// strip.invariant.group and launder.invariant.group intrinsics.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00707" /><CodeLine lineNumber="707"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00708" /><CodeLine lineNumber="708"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// If \\p ExternalAnalysis is provided it will be used to calculate a offset</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="709"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// when a operand of GEP is not constant.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For example, for a value \\p ExternalAnalysis might try to calculate a</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// lower bound. If \\p ExternalAnalysis is successful, it should return true.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// If this is called on a non-pointer value, it returns &#39;this&#39; and the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\p Offset is not modified.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Note that this function will never return a nullptr. It will also never</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// manipulate the \\p Offset in a way that would not match the difference</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// between the underlying value and the returned one. Thus, if no constant</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// offset was found, the returned value is the underlying one and \\p Offset</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00720" /><CodeLine lineNumber="720"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// is unchanged.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
